# SeleniumTestProject1

## Overview
This project demonstrates a testing framework that supports Behavior Driven Development (BDD) for automation testing of web applications using Java, Selenium, Cucumber, and Serenity BDD.

## Project Structure
- src/main/java/pageobjects: Contains Page Object Model classes.
- HomePage.java:             Represents the home page and includes methods to interact with it.
- CareersPage.java:          Represents the careers page and includes methods to interact with it.
- JobSearchPage.java:        Represents the job search page and includes methods to interact with it.
- src/test/java/steps:       Contains step definition classes.
- JobSearchSteps.java:       Defines the steps corresponding to the scenarios in the feature file.
- src/test/java/tests:       Contains test classes.
- JobSearchTest.java:        Contains test methods for job search functionality.
- src/test/java/utils:       Contains utility classes.
- ConfigLoader.java:         Loads configuration properties.
- Logger.java:               Provides logging functionality.
- PopupHandler.java:         Handles popup windows.
- BrowserUtils.java:         Provides browser-related utilities.
- WaitUtils.java:            Provides wait-related utilities.
- ScreenshotUtils.java:      Provides screenshot-related utilities.
- src/test/resources/features: Contains Cucumber feature files.
- job_search.feature:          Defines the job search scenarios in Gherkin syntax.
- src/test/resources:           Contains configuration files.
- config.properties:            Stores configuration settings.

## Technologies
- Java
- Selenium
- Cucumber
- TestNG
- Serenity BDD

## Setup
1. Clone the repository.
2. Install dependencies using Maven.
3. Update the path to chromedriver in config file
4. Run the tests using TestNG.

## Running Tests
To run the tests, use the following command:
```bash
mvn test / mvn clean verify / or right clock test runner and run scenario

## Reporting
   Test results are handled by Serenity BDD and can be found in the target/site/serenity directory.
